        public V put(K key,

        Specified by:
        put in interface java.util.Map<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
        Returns:
        a)If key is non-null and was not previously in the table, add the entry and return null. b)If key is non-null and was previously in the table, add the entry and return the old value (the one that was just overwritten). c)If key is null, throw a NullPointerException immediately. On average, this should happen in O(1) time. Remember that you will have to resize when the max load factor is exceeded; that is, if the max load factor is .75 and the current load factor is also .75, do not resize.
